<title type="html"><![CDATA[spliting GENESIS binarys and using 8bit eproms?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8587&amp;p=89639#p89639"><![CDATA[
Don't do it. Use a 27C160. It solders directly into most PCBs. Sega did not alter pinouts like Nintendo. Also the game mentioned is 2 megabytes, not 1. You'd need 8 of those 2 megabit chips for a 16 megabit game.<br /><br />You can simulate a 16bit eprom with two 8bit chips but again this is silly. Just buy a 16bit programming adapter if you have to do so or just get someone to program a 27C160 for you.<br /><br />Or just buy a EverDrive MD, one of the best Flash carts out there, and the best for Sega Genesis easily. <br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://krikzz.com/everdrive-md.html">http://krikzz.com/everdrive-md.html</a><!-- m --><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://shop.retrogate.com/Everdrive-MD-EDMD.htm">http://shop.retrogate.com/Everdrive-MD-EDMD.htm</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1726">MottZilla</a> — Sun Feb 05, 2012 10:54 pm</p><hr />
